FBIS4-51864 "dreas086_c_94018" FBIS-EAS-94-086 Daily Report 2 May 1994 North Korea Indian Official Interviewed on Korean Army Day Indian Official Interviewed on Korean Army Day SK0205215594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1503 GMT 2 May 94 SK0205215594 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Under the wise guidance of the great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il, the Korean people and People's Army are defending the sovereignty of the country and the gains of socialism with honour, smashing the war manoeuvres of the imperialists and [words indistinct] general secretary of the Democratic Youth Federation of India, in an interview with the KCNA reporter in India on April 18 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army. The general secretary said Comrade Kim Chong-il possessed of rare wisdom and outstanding ability of leadership, has not only built an invincible anthropocentric socialism based on the singlehearted unity of the leader, the party and the masses but also put forward unique idea and theory of Army building and consolidated the defences of the country as firm as rock. The secret of the victory won by the Korean people and People's Army at every step in the decisive battle with U.S. imperialism and its allied force in recent years lies in the outstanding leadership of Comrade Kim Chong-il, supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, who is possessed of iron will and matchless grit, he emphasized. Saying that the acute situation created on the Korean peninsula is entirly attributable to the reckless military adventures and interference of the United States, he demanded that the U.S. withdraw its forces from South Korea, discontinue all forms of war rehearsals and stop the deployment of Patriot missiles in South Korea at once.
